Senayan Aquatic Stadium for IND(ONE)SIA
Well, I think athletes are like Indonesian sport's hero. Since this month is SEA GAMES and today is Independence Day, let's support our athletes who already give their time and energy to present our country. Most of the people only remember their achievement, but don't care about the process (and I do to, sometimes). Well, I guess that's one of many other reasons why I choose this project. At least, by designing it, I can be more aware, understand and care about what they do and how they do it. .

Perjalanan mendaki Sinai menuju lokasi yang menurut "tradisi" merupakan tempat Nabi Musa menerima 2 loh batu dari Allah, ditemani oleh Ahmad, seorang keturunan Suku Bedouin. Suku Bedouin adalah etnis yang tinggal di tenda-tenda sekitar pegunungan (Sinai) dan nomaden. Mayoritasnya adalah beragama Muslim, tetapi di tengah bulan Ramadhan nan suci, mereka dengan senang hati menemani kami, kaum nasrani, untuk berjalan kaki mendaki dan menurun. caption.text:
<GARAGE Pavilion>

Moscow have a lot of unique building. The oldest until the newest. For an architecture student, Moscow's building lead us to study architecture of its own way. 
This is one of the new building that they have. It's a pavilion made by one of the pritzker prize winner, Shigeru Ban. This temporary building was built in the area of Gorky Park. Like usual, he used his signature material, paper tube and cardboard. With total area 2,400 meter square and 6 meters height, this building has mesmerized people by the shape and column rhythm. 
This pavilion used to be an exhibition art, lecture, workshop, book store with cafe. It was a pleasure to really see these art-work rather than only see it in my teacher's presentation. 
#explore_russia #architecture #instatravel #2015
